The music player

Music in Old School RuneScape is mostly in-game background music designed to enhance a player's gaming experience and fit with the environment the avatar is in. Music in Old School RuneScape draws inspiration from classical and world music. These are unlocked during gameplay by going to a particular place or completing a quest.

An in-game counter at the bottom of the interface can be used to check how many tracks players have unlocked. Players who unlock all non-holiday music tracks will be able to purchase the music cape from Olaf the Bard, and subsequently unlock the Air Guitar emote.

To unlock Holiday event music from all past years, players must complete the current year's event for that holiday. As of 23 March 2022, there are a total of 683 music tracks (not including unlisted & unused music) found in Old School RuneScape.

Note: On 6 March 2007, RuneScape's existing music tracks were updated as part of an audio rework; Old School uses these reworked tracks. The original versions can be found under the "Versions" section of articles for music tracks released prior to March 2007.

  • On 7 June 2016, the unlisted track Massacre was removed from the game.
  • On 7 June 2018, Clan Wars was updated as it was incorrectly using pianos instead of drums.
  • On 26 September 2019, the unused tracks Game Intro 1, Ambience 2, Ambience 3, Ambience 4, and Fade Test were removed from the game.
  • On 23 April 2020, Predator Xarpus, Arachnids of Vampyrium and Dance of the Nylocas were all reworked.
  • On 4 June 2020, Conspiracy was extended in length while Distant Land was slightly changed.

Trivia[edit | edit source]

  • Old School RuneScape has various unused songs, such as Athlete's Foot, Autumn in Bridgelum and an unfinished version of The Adventurer. These songs are usually either temporary event songs, or remnants of songs intended for release after 2007.
  • The shortest music track is Snowflake and My Arm, at 01:17 in length, while the longest song is Museum Medley, at 11:10 in length.

'''Music''' in ''[[Old School RuneScape]]'' is mostly in-game background music designed to enhance a player's gaming experience and fit with the environment the avatar is in. Music in ''Old School RuneScape'' draws inspiration from classical and world music. These are unlocked during gameplay by going to a particular [[locations|place]] or completing a [[quest]].

An in-game counter at the bottom of the interface can be used to check how many tracks players have unlocked. Players who unlock all non-[[holiday]] music tracks will be able to purchase the [[music cape]] from [[Olaf the Bard]], and subsequently unlock the [[Air Guitar]] [[emote]].

To unlock [[Holiday event]] music from all past years, players must complete the current year's event for that holiday. As of {{globals|latest music release date}}, there are a total of {{Globals|music tracks}} music tracks (not including [[Unlisted music tracks|unlisted & unused music]]) found in ''Old School RuneScape''.

''Note:'' On 6 March 2007, ''RuneScape'''s existing music tracks were [[March 2007 audio rework|updated]] as part of an audio rework; ''Old School'' uses these reworked tracks. The original versions can be found under the "Versions" section of articles for music tracks released prior to March 2007.

==Updated tracks==
The following tracks have been updated since ''Old School RuneScape'' was released:
*On [[26 February]] [[2015]], the original unused version of [[The Trade Parade]] was replaced with the present version using updated instruments.
*On [[7 June]] [[2016]], the unlisted track [[Massacre]] was removed from the game.
*On [[7 June]] [[2018]], [[Clan Wars (music track)|Clan Wars]] was updated as it was incorrectly using pianos instead of drums.
*On [[26 September]] [[2019]], the unused tracks [[Game Intro 1]], [[Ambience 2]], [[Ambience 3]], [[Ambience 4]], and [[Fade Test]] were removed from the game.
*On [[23 April]] [[2020]], [[Predator Xarpus]], [[Arachnids of Vampyrium]] and [[Dance of the Nylocas]] were all reworked.
*On [[4 June]] [[2020]], [[Conspiracy]] was extended in length while [[Distant Land]] was slightly changed.

==Trivia==
* ''Old School RuneScape'' has various unused songs, such as [[Athlete's Foot]], [[Autumn in Bridgelum]] and an unfinished version of [[The Adventurer]]. These songs are usually either temporary event songs, or remnants of songs intended for release after 2007.
* The shortest music track is ''Snowflake and My Arm'', at 01:17 in length, while the longest song is ''Museum Medley'', at 11:10 in length.
